relation: Darrow3 - #12 Remember, the next time you attempt to microwave a burrito, make sure you are not accidentally activating a nuclear device. It happens more often than you may think.
Darrow3 - #13 As a more lighthearted mood greets our heroes, a monkey comes crashing right along with it. It seems this is merely a prelude to something...incredibly random.
Darrow3 - #14 After having dealt with a strange monkey, what next but a strange delivery man? As for that poor package, well...don't worry. The contents are better off being broken, to be honest.
Darrow3 - #15 Yet another strange encounter occurs as a maid suddenly drops in after having ease-dropped on the previous conversation. Who would have thought trout-flavored yogurt was all the rage?

Darrow3 - #16 Two boys, a chicken, and a mouse board a bus heading to the desert so that they can retrieve a trout-flavored yogurt making machine which is key to their success in saving the world and is in the hands of monkeys that live out in the hole in a desert with an old man who teaches them how to teleport so they can give the machine to a maid who will let them bypass security and save their friend from an evil fat kid and an old man who are working for a demonic alien who is becoming the embodiment of evil itself. Earthbound!
